#import "../../lib.typ": chapter

#chapter(2, "A complicated relationship")[
  As the brief spring vacation coming to a close, the gentle spring winds of
  April knocked on the closed window, signalling the beginning of a new school
  year. Outside the bedroom window, the birds were chirping under the cherry
  blossoms, which were lightly swayed by the gentle spring wind.

  Mona was sound asleep in her bed, after yet another long night of watching
  idol performances. It had become a routine at this point: After returning home
  from a live show at 8 PM, she spent the entire night with her eyes glued to
  the TV screen, before finally going to bed at 3 AM.

  It was six o'clock in the morning, so the girl had just been resting for a mere
  three hours.
  Usually, she would wake up at noon for her lunch -- which to her might be more
  like a breakfast -- then spend
  the entire afternoon watching the pre-recorded shows that she missed during
  sleep, while periodically
  checking up on the recent idol updates in her phone.

  For a young girl in her developing ages like Mona, this looked like a terrible
  schedule to follow. From the complaints that Mona usually received from her
  parents, it seemed like staying up late could cause a host of problem, ranging
  from reducing productivity during the day to getting pimples. The latter,
  especially, was a pretty problematic for teenagers in puberty like Mona,
  though the girl did not really mind it that much except for the annoying pain
  going with it.

  Despite knowing of her daughter's chaotic daily routine, her parents mostly
  turned a blind eye. They would throw some complaints here and there, but that
  was as far as it could. Well, there were reasons for this. Firstly, they
  were already having
  their hands full with work. And Mona was not a small child anymore to start
  with, so her parents could not afford to worry about every little thing she
  does. And secondly, and more importantly,
  this hectic schedule was just a temporary thing for
  the ongoing two-week spring vacation. Therefore, everyone would expect that
  once this two-week time period passed, everything would return to normal.
  Hopefully.

  Mona's room stayed silent and peaceful, but there was a feeling of uneaseness.
  As if there was something that would soon disturb this peace.

  At first, it was just a series of footsteps going up the stairs,
  originating from outside the
  room. It was initially hard to make out these noises, but they were becoming
  increasingly louder. It felt like a scene from a horror movie, with all the
  suspension building up to a climax.

  "Mona, wake up! Today is your first day of high school, right?"

  Disrupting the scenery of a peaceful April morning was a figure of a girl who
  barged right into Mona’s room. Leaving the door wide open, she let in a gust
  of wind, which completely destroyed the tranquil atmosphere.

  Having long blonde twintails and a cute face, the girl who just entered seemed
  like the perfect
  representation of an ideal high school girl. Or at least that was who she used
  to be.

  And it was Narumi Sena, Mona's big
  sister. She had just taken a shower after her daily morning jog, just in time
  to wake up her younger sister.

  Sena lifted the curtains and opened the window,
  filling the entire room with sunlight of a brand-new day. As the spring breeze
  swirled her short hair, Mona finally awakened from what seems like an eternal
  slumber.

  "You stayed up late watching TV again?" Sena, after seeing how sluggish her
  sister's movements were, complained, "Didn't mom tell you to go to bed early
  for school?"

  "Good morning, sis…" said Mona as she rubbed her eyes.

  Even though she acted sleepy, Mona had been half-awake from a while ago.
  Back when the footsteps of her sister was approaching her room,
  she prayed under her blanket that
  it was just her mind playing tricks on her, before having to face the truth
  that the annoying humanoid alarm clock had gotten to her.

  She had just slept for three hours, barely enough for her to last the day.
  The sheer fatigue made her deeply regret
  the decision for staying up till 3 AM. It could not be helped, however, as
  Asunatan was just too captivating, after all.

  Now, having to face the failures of her ways, Mona tried to open her left
  eye, which, by her own experience, was slightly better than the right one at
  handling bright lights. Nevertheless, the blinding lights originating from
  the window were just too powerful for her to handle.
  It was not until five minutes later that she finally
  adjusted her eyes to be able to see things. Hazily, that was.

  Sena looked at her younger sister with a mild irritation, before switching her
  focus to the set of uniform hanging on the door. She had stayed up late the
  last night to prepare it, so seeing the uniform without any wrinkles put a
  smile on her face.

  However, more than anything, what excited her was the mere thought of her
  sister wearing it.

  "Hurry up and wear your new uniform. Hmph\~\~ I can’t wait to see my little
  angel in her new sailor outfits!", Sena said with a clear display of
  enthusiasm on her face.

  Even though Mona could barely open one of her eyes, she could clearly see the
  sheer amount of anticipation her sister had for this day. It was really
  frightening, to be honest.

  Sena took down the uniform neatly hanging at the door and put it by Mona's
  bed. The set was ironed out to perfection, which implied that Sena must
  have taken quite a lot of time preparing last night. Overkill or not, it was
  clear that she wanted to see Mona with the best appearance in her first day of
  high school.

  Meanwhile, Mona, the subject in question, did not really care about it that much.
  Of course being attractive would attract more people, she knew that, but in
  her opinion, what mattered more was the personality and maybe the charisma,
  rather than the appearance or first impressions.
  Even though she was a girl, beauty was one of
  the things that Mona had the least interest in. Nevertheless, she still found
  looking at cute girls and guys a fun thing to do, she just did not care about
  her own appearances.

  She took a look at the sailor uniform by her bed. Her sister was too hyped for
  something as trivial as her first day of high school, she thought.

  For her, this is just an inherent step of her life. It was not really a sign
  of maturity, as going to high school
  does not magically make someone more grown-up or anything. It was just a
  milestone celebrated on by those who have nothing else to really care about,
  or so she thought.

  "Okay, okay." Mona got up from bed, took the uniform that had been carefully
  prepared by her sister, and got straight into the bathroom
  to change her clothes.

  Usually, she would just change her clothes right in her room, but she
  refrained from doing so because of her sister's presence.
  Changing in front of such
  a hyper-energetic Sena would ultimately lead to physical contact, which was
  extremely annoying for her. The last time she let her guard down,
  even those two of hers that were still
  developing were not spared from being touched. It was nothing but hell.

  As an effort to make these painful memories fade away, Mona took a quick look
  at herself after changing into her new set of uniform.
  For her, it is still unbelievable that she was actually wearing it
  right now.

  Her middle school uniform was also a sailor-style uniform, but the colors were
  a little bit different. The top part, including the white loose blouse and the
  iconic blue sailor-style collar had its colors swapped compared to her old suit.
  The pleated skirt, even though it had a similar dark tint to the middle school
  uniform, but the color was a little more on the blue side.

  To Mona, even though her new uniform was just a different coloring of her middle
  school's set, it just did not feel the same way.

  After Mona finished changing, she opened the bathroom door and prepared for
  the worst. As expected, she was instantly met with her sister’s intense gaze.

  "So cute! You are truly an angel!!!!" just as Sena exclaimed, she jumped
  towards Mona and hugged her little sister, leaving Mona with no room to
  breathe.

  "Stop..., big sis! You will ruin my uniform!"

  "Oh right!" Sena immediately released Mona from her tight embrace, "I can not
  ruin your first high school impression. I spent so much time ironing that
  outfit for you last night, after all."

  Of course, Mona really don’t care much about the state of her uniform,
  her woeful cries were nothing but an attempt to escape the painful grip of her
  sister. Nevertheless, she was surprised of the fact that her silly little
  excuse actually worked and granted her the freedom she desired.

  "Well then, I will go get breakfast now."

  Mona walked downstairs, unsurprised by the boundless obsession her sister had
  for her. It was just another day for her, it seemed.

  "Wait for me! Mona!", Sena yelled as she chased after her little sister.

  Back when Mona was a little girl, she did not really mind the intense love her
  sister had for her really much. In fact, the two used to be very close, spending
  time together for as long as they could remember.

  But as she got older, she began to feel some form of annoyance towards her sister.
  She did not like how tight the hugs had become. She did not like how she
  always became the topic of her sister’s discussions at school. And especially,
  she did not like how her sister always bought all sorts of so-called "cute
  clothes" that looked more like a clown costume and expect her to wear it.

  But it was not like that she hated her sister.
  She simply had developed a cold front towards Sena. If this were a light novel,
  the readers would describe Mona as a stereotypical _tsundere_,
  but Mona really had no choice other than to conceal her emotions like this.

  As for Sena, she in fact knew everything.
  She knew that her sister had grown out of the age of being so physical all the
  time, but she just could not help it but to hug her when she got the chance.
  Regarding the cold front that Mona always showed her, she was aware that it was
  just a front to keep her away.
  However, she was not detered by it at all,
  if anything, this gave her even more reasons to act clingy
  to Mona. Seeing her dear sister concealing her real emotions made her cuteness
  tenfold after all.

  Even though the two had such a complicated relationship, there was one thing
  that had never changed.

  Which is how much they treasured each other.

  They say siblings always have some sort of complicated relationships, which
  seems to apply here as well.
]
